CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 21, 1950, pg. 2, reads: "Featured at YW - Mrs. Eunice D. Washington, a librarian at Wylie Avenue Branch Carnegie Library, is now being featured in a series of sparkling book reviews at the Centre Avenue Branch YWCA held each Tuesday morning at 10:30.  The public is invited to attend the series, which includes discussions on classic and contemporary works. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Librarian Eunice D. Washington posed in front of fiction section in Carnegie Library, Hill District branch
